    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with a clear emphasis on maximizing stolen base potential and leveraging high-leverage platoon advantages. **Kyle Tucker** (76.99) and **Jackson Merrill** (75.10) stand as our most potent options. **Kyle Tucker** benefits from a steady matchup against Leiter, while **Jackson Merrill** is a priority play due to a favorable wind forecast and a soft matchup against Feltner; his ability to exploit the pitcher\u2019s slow delivery significantly boosts his utility in our scarcity-driven roster construction. **Gunnar Henderson** (70.87) also earns a strong recommendation; despite facing a high-skill arm in Logan Webb, his leadoff spot and dynamic platoon advantage make him a foundational piece of today\u2019s offensive strategy.\n\nWe are navigating several complex platoon dynamics, most notably with **Luis Robert Jr.** (62.03) and **Nolan Schanuel** (64.66). **Luis Robert Jr.** earns a boost from a favorable platoon shift, though we remain mindful of his catcher-speed profile. **Nolan Schanuel** benefits immensely from the weak 5.28 xERA of Williamson, providing a safe, high-floor output in a favorable pitching environment. The tightest decision on the bench involved **Marcell Ozuna** (52.05), who finished just outside the starting rotation. While **Marcell Ozuna** provided a respectable efficiency score, the optimizer prioritized the higher ceiling of **Heliot Ramos** and **Andy Pages**, both of whom project better in their respective park-factor-adjusted environments. \n\nRisk management remains a priority given the caliber of opposing arms. While **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (52.92) is active, his matchup against Joe Ryan presents a stiff challenge that suppresses his efficiency score compared to his typical baseline. We are effectively sitting players like **Coby Mayo** and **Josh Jung**, whose scores fell below our 40.0 floor due to poor matchups against elite arms like Webb and Sheehan. We continue to monitor 